{"File":"/home/ketan/eagerminds-task/.gemini/transcript","LineNumber":5,"LineContent":"      \"content\": \"\u003cUSER_REQUEST\u003e\\nWe are building a Bookmarks Web Application using Next.js (App Router), TypeScript, and Supabase. \\n\\nimplement the baseline Authentication system:\\n1. Create a Supabase server client, client-side browser helper, and middleware configuration to handle cookie-based user sessions seamlessly (using @supabase/ssr).\\n2. Build clean, responsive UI layouts for both /login and /signup pages under the src/app/ directory using Tailwind CSS.\\n3. Configure the signup flow to leverage our Resend API key (RESEND_API_KEY) from our existing .env.local file to trigger a structured \\\"Welcome to Bookmarks\\\" email using a standard fetch/API call upon a successful user creation event.\\n4. Set up an authentication check inside the middleware so that unauthenticated users are automatically redirected away from the /dashboard route back to /login.\\n\\nVerify your file layout when finished. Do not create the database tables or write the bookmarks data schema layouts yet.\\n\u003c/USER_REQUEST\u003e\\n\u003cADDITIONAL_METADATA\u003e\\nThe current local time is: 2026-06-05T22:06:33+05:30.\\n\u003c/ADDITIONAL_METADATA\u003e\\n\u003cUSER_SETTINGS_CHANGE\u003e\\nThe user changed setting `Model Selection` from None to Claude Opus 4.6 (Thinking). No need to comment on this change if the user doesn't ask about it. If reporting what model you are, please use a human readable name instead of the exact string.\\n\u003c/USER_SETTINGS_CHANGE\u003e\""}
