{"File":"/home/ketan/eagerminds-task/.gemini/transcript","LineNumber":385,"LineContent":"      \"content\": \"To run the project locally, follow these steps:\\n\\n### 1. Configure Environment Variables\\nOpen the [.env.local](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/.env.local) file. If you want to test the welcome email delivery on signup, replace the placeholder value for `RESEND_API_KEY` with your actual API key:\\n```env\\nRESEND_API_KEY=your_actual_resend_api_key_here\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Start the Development Server\\nRun the following command in the project root directory:\\n```bash\\nnpm run dev\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Open the Application\\nOnce the dev server is running, you can visit the pages in your browser:\\n- **Sign Up**: `http://localhost:3000/signup` (leads to signup page [signup/page.tsx](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/app/signup/page.tsx))\\n- **Log In**: `http://localhost:3000/login` (leads to login page [login/page.tsx](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/app/login/page.tsx))\\n- **Dashboard**: `http://localhost:3000/dashboard` (leads to dashboard page [dashboard/page.tsx](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/app/dashboard/page.tsx))\\n\\n\u003e [!NOTE]\\n\u003e The `/dashboard` route is protected. If you try to visit it while unauthenticated, the custom proxy middleware in [proxy.ts](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/proxy.ts) will automatically redirect you back to `/login`.\""}
{"File":"/home/ketan/eagerminds-task/.gemini/transcript","LineNumber":489,"LineContent":"      \"content\": \"The environment variables and API keys for the project are defined in the **[.env.local](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/.env.local)** file located in the root directory of the project.\\n\\nIt currently contains the following keys:\\n```env\\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://udotkjqnsqjpfzttegks.supabase.co\\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_UVnEv5kDv4_T1BcCdV8reA_iQBuT41A\\nRESEND_API_KEY=your_actual_resend_api_key_here\\n```\""}
{"File":"/home/ketan/eagerminds-task/.gemini/transcript","LineNumber":641,"LineContent":"      \"content\": \"Since \\\"this\\\" could refer either to **Entire** (the session tracking tool) or **Next.js** (the application runtime), here is how both handle the `.env.local` file:\\n\\n### 1. Does Entire read/track the `.env.local` file?\\n**No, and it is intentionally configured not to.** \\nBecause `.env.local` contains sensitive credentials (like your `RESEND_API_KEY`), it is listed in your [.gitignore](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/.gitignore) file (line 34: `.env*`).\\n\\nEntire is a Git-integrated tool and automatically respects all `.gitignore` rules to prevent credentials from being logged, indexed, or committed.\\n\\n**How to confirm:**\\nYou can run the Git check-ignore command in the terminal to verify that Git (and Entire) is ignoring it:\\n```bash\\ngit check-ignore -v .env.local\\n```\\nThis will output:\\n```text\\n.gitignore:34:.env*     .env.local\\n```\\n*(Indicating it is ignored by line 34 of `.gitignore`)*\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. Does Next.js read/load the `.env.local` file?\\n**Yes.** Next.js is configured by default to automatically load all environment variables from `.env.local` at startup.\\n\\n**How to confirm:**\\n1. Start the development server (`npm run dev`).\\n2. Try signing up a new user on `http://localhost:3000/signup`. \\n3. If Next.js reads the key successfully, the signup page will trigger the welcome email using your `RESEND_API_KEY`. If the key is missing or not read, the terminal running `npm run dev` will output an error stating that the Resend API key is invalid or missing.\""}
