ion handler\\n24:     \\u251c\\u2500\\u2500 login/\\n25:     \\u2502   \\u2514\\u2500\\u2500 page.tsx                  \\u2190 Login page UI\\n26:     \\u251c\\u2500\\u2500 signup/\\n27:     \\u2502   \\u2514\\u2500\\u2500 page.tsx                  \\u2190 Signup page UI\\n28:     \\u2514\\u2500\\u2500 dashboard/\\n29:         \\u2514\\u2500\\u2500 page.tsx                  \\u2190 Protected page (minimal placeholder)\\n30: ```\\n31: \\n32: ## Architecture Decisions\\n33: \\n34: ### 1. Supabase Client Layer (`@supabase/ssr` v0.10.3)\\n35: \\n36: | Helper | File | Used In |\\n37: |--------|------|---------|\\n38: | `createBrowserClient` \\n\u003ctruncated 390 bytes\u003e\\n/lib/supabase/middleware.ts) | Proxy \\u2014 wires `request.cookies` \\u2192 `response.cookies` |\\n41: \\n42: \u003e [!IMPORTANT]\\n43: \u003e The v0.10.x `setAll` callback now receives a **second `headers` argument** containing anti-caching headers. These are forwarded to the response in the proxy helper.\\n44: \\n45: ### 2. Next.js 16 Proxy (formerly Middleware)\\n46: \\n47: The [proxy.ts](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/proxy.ts) file uses the **new `proxy` export** (the `middleware` convention is deprecated in Next.js 16). The matcher excludes `_next/static`, `_next/image`, and metadata files.\\n48: \\n49: **Auth guard logic** lives in [middleware.ts](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/lib/supabase/middleware.ts#L60-L66):\\n50: - Calls `supabase.auth.getUser()` to refresh tokens\\n51: - If no user AND path starts with `/dashboard` \\u2192 redirect to `/login`\\n52: \\n53: ### 3. Login \u0026 Signup Flows\\n54: \\n55: Both pages use **Server Actions** ([auth.ts](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/app/actions/auth.ts)) and the `\u003cform action={...}\u003e` pattern:\\n56: \\n57: - **Login**: `signInWithPassword` \\u2192 redirect to `/dashboard`\\n58: - **Signup**: `signUp` with `display_name` metadata \\u2192 fire welcome email \\u2192 redirect with confirmation message\\n59: \\n60: ### 4. Welcome Email (Resend)\\n61: \\n62: The [welcome-email route](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/app/api/welcome-email/route.ts) uses a standard `fetch` call to the Resend API. It sends a rich HTML email with dark-themed branding. Called fire-and-forget from the signup action.\\n63: \\n64: ### 5. Auth Callback\\n65: \\n66: [callback/route.ts](file:///home/ketan/eagerminds-task/src/app/auth/callback/route.ts) handles the PKCE code exchange after email confirmation or OAuth redirects.\\n67: \\n68: ## What Was NOT Created (per instructions)\\n69: \\n70: - \\u274c Database tables / bookmarks schema\\n71: - \\u274c Bookmarks CRUD\\n72: - \\u274c Any data models\\n73: \\n74: ## TypeScript Status\\n75: \\n76: \\u2705 `tsc --noEmit` passes with **zero errors**.\\n77: \\nThe above content shows the entire, complete file contents of the requested file.\\n\""}
